    "The performance of optimized GAN (Goel et al. 2021) is compared with the baseline CGAN.",
    "The generated images are used with training images for classification tasks.",
    "So, the F1-score and accuracy of 98.79% and 98.78% respectively are achieved with Optimized GAN while 91.60% accuracy and 90.99% F1-score are achieved with the baseline CGAN.",
    "It shows that Optimized GAN can perform better with accuracy and F1-score measures, as well as in optimizing hyperparameters for a balanced GAN.",
    "In this section, technical papers of GANs are reviewed to address the non-convergence problem in the domain of biomedical imagery."
